header.gameNote: ATLANTIC SUN TR AT JOHNSON CITY TN

article.headline: Stetson 54, Fla Atlantic 44
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Anthony Register scored 20 points as Stetson continued its late-season run with a 54-44 victory over Florida Atlantic in the Atlantic Sun Conference tournament quarterfinals Thursday night. Stetson (14-17), which has won 12 of its last 13 games after starting the season 2-16, takes on second-seeded Belmont in Saturday's semifinals. Register made seven of his first eight shots. E.J. Gordon, who has averaged 18.1 points a game during Stetson's resurgence, added 14 points and moved into the top 10 on the Atlantic Sun career scoring list. The third-seeded Owls (15-13) came in on a four-game winning streak. It was the final appearance in the Atlantic Sun for Florida Atlantic, which is moving to the Sun Belt Conference. DeAndre Rice scored 13 points to lead Florida Atlantic. Stetson led 31-20 at halftime and increased the advantage to 13 points when Register connected from 3-point range with 17:10 left. Florida Atlantic cut the deficit to single digits, but never got closer than six the rest of the way. Stetson missed four of eight free throws in the final minute, but Florida Atlantic couldn't take advantage.
